title: For Sale:  EAA Witness 45 ACP Auto Pistol
postcontent: The EAA Witness pistols have been around for several years now, and have gained a lot of respect from knowledgeable shooters. Built by Tanfoglio in Italy, the Witness is a close copy of the excellent CZ 75 design, modernized a bit and chambered for some pretty powerful cartridges, such as the 45 ACP and the 10mm Auto. The Witness uses a wide body magazine, and in the 45 ACP version shown here, holds ten cartridges, for a total loaded capacity of eleven rounds. Still, with the higher capacity than many 45 ACP steel pistols, the Witness is comfortable in most hands, and I find it to be extremely comfortable in mine.

title: For Sale:  1911 – 22LR
postcontent:
Great 1911 model chambered in 22 LR!  I believe the Chiappa Company operates in the US out of Ohio and the 1911- 22LR is made in Italy by Chiappa Armi Sports Ltd.
Fits into any 1911-style holster. Has all the bells and whistles as the 45 ACP and uses 22 LR ammo for less recoil and less expense shooting. Makes a great 1911 trainer with affordable ammo or field-carry gun for small game -- or just plain plinking fun.
Constructed from an alloy called Chiappalloy and feels like the real deal, adding to the overall heft of the gun. With castings built in many cases to the exact specifications found on the Colt 1911, the overall feel and balance is very similar the classic Colt 1911. (A genuine 1911 designed from the ground up – not a converted plastic toy or paintball gun. Does not use the plastic parts or pot metal found on some 22 LR imitators.)
Safeties include the traditional 1911 left-handed thumb safety that blocks the slide and trigger as well as a firing-pin safety.
The grip angle is the same as the legendary 45 ACP Model 1911.
The 5-inch, fixed barrel is quality steel that is part of the frame – forming a solid piece of metal that produces excellent accuracy and a stable feel. Also easy to field strip because of the fixed barrel.
Sharp looking walnut grips are laser-checkered and remind you of vintage walnut grip panels. Very comfortable to hold and look good against the black finish.
It’s easy to work the slide to chamber a round (a plus for those who lack hand strength due to an injury or arthritis).
Shot this gun with expensive ammo and bulk ammo – I was impressed either way. Surprised me how well it grouped at 25 yards!
